    "body": "Hi @Sirbuland, thanks for getting this to our attention, this indeed is a bug, which we managed to reduce thanks to your example. It's happening because 3.5.1 we made a change in how we deal with default values coming from URLs. \r\n\r\nCan you try this out in 3.4.0 of InstantSearch.js? You can use yarn resolutions to force that version to be used.",
